Having ensured the continued existence of all these institutions with a capital of 12 thousand rubles, Golovnin transferred them to the jurisdiction of the Pronsky Zemstvo. Golovnin published: “Notes on two churches near the village of Gulynkakh” (St. elementary schools near the village of Gulynkakh" (St. Petersburg, 1874); the works of his father, Vice-Admiral Golovnin, were published. Golovnin was one of the first members of the Russian Geographical Society, in which he was secretary from 1845 to 1847. He died in his house on Gagarinskaya Embankment, 20.